<td valign="top" width="413">
<img src="images/sections.gif" width="167" height="7" alt="Documentary Sections" border="0">
<br>
<font class="subhead"><a href="bitter.html"  class="highlight">Bitter Times</a><br></font><font class="body">Jim Crow laws robbed African Americans of basic rights.
<P>
<font class="subhead"><a href="danger.html" class="highlight">Danger, Violence, Exploitation</a><br></font><font class="body">
Blacks in the Jim Crow South faced lynchings, insults and thievery at the hands of whites.
<p>
<font class="subhead"><a href="veil.html"  class="highlight">Communities "Behind the Veil"</a><br></font><font class="body">African Americans built vital social institutions to fight segregation and uplift the race. 
<p>

<font class="subhead"><a href="past.html"  class="highlight">Keeping the Past</a><br></font><font class="body">Black families used oral storytelling and photography to pass along their memories of slavery and Reconstruction. 
<p>
<font class="subhead"><a href="resistance.html"  class="highlight">Resistance</a><br></font><font class="body">Many African Americans found subtle ways to combat the humiliation and economic hardship imposed by Jim Crow. 

<p>
<font class="subhead"><a href="whites.html"  class="highlight">Whites Remember Jim Crow</a><br></font><font class="body">
In the southwestern Louisiana town of New Iberia, older whites say race relations were more peaceful during Jim Crow than they are now.
<p>


<img src="images/more.gif" width="167" height="11" "More on Jim Crow" border="0" vspace="5"><br>

<font class="body_link"><a href="laws.html" class="highlight">Jim Crow Laws</a></font>
<br>A sampling of repressive Jim Crow laws.
<p>
<font class="body_link"><a href="resources.html" class="highlight">Resources</a></font><br>
Informants, documentary audio and transcript, links, and books. 

